Found it. TanStack Start needs a deployment preset for Vercel. The `tanstackStart()` plugin has no preset configured, so it's building for the wrong target.

Update `web/vite.config.ts`:

```ts
tanstackStart({
  preset: 'vercel'
})
```

Or you may need to create `web/app.config.ts`:

```ts
import { defineConfig } from '@tanstack/react-start/config'

export default defineConfig({
  server: {
    preset: 'vercel',
  },
})
```

The TanStack Start docs should confirm which approach is current for your version. Want me to check the docs?

Found it. You need to create `web/app.config.ts`:

```ts
// app.config.ts
import { defineConfig } from '@tanstack/start/config'

export default defineConfig({
  server: {
    preset: 'vercel',
  },
})
```

This tells TanStack Start (which uses Nitro under the hood) to build for Vercel's serverless platform.

**Sources:**
- [TanStack Start on Vercel](https://vercel.com/docs/frameworks/full-stack/tanstack-start)
- [Hosting | TanStack Start React Docs](https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/hosting)

